data.chText: 未经正式批准的；非官方的；非正式的
data.enText: that does not have permission or approval from sb in authority

data.chText: 未经批准的协议 / 罢工
非官方的估计数字为200万以上。
data.enText: Unofficial estimates put the figure at over two million.

data.chText: 非公事的；私事的；私人的
data.enText: that is not part of sb's official business

data.chText: 前总统到中国进行了私人访问。
data.enText: The former president paid an unofficial visit to China.

simple_means.memory_skill: un 不，无 + official 官方的 → 非官方的

tr: not having official authority or sanction
example: he participated in an unofficial capacity
the early election returns are unofficial

value.def: An unofficial action or statement is not organized or approved by a person or group in authority.

example.ex: Staff voted to continue an unofficial strike in support of seven colleagues who were dismissed last week...
example.tran: 职工投票决定继续进行非正式罢工，以支持上周被解雇的7名同事。

example.ex: Official reports put the death toll at under one hundred, but unofficial estimates speak of at least two hundred dead.
example.tran: 官方报道说死亡人数在100人以下，但非官方估计至少有200人死亡。

value.tran: 非官方的；未经正式批准的；非正式的

example.ex: Some workers are legally employed, but the majority work unofficially with neither health nor wage security.
example.tran: 虽然一些工人是合法雇用的，但大部分工人都是非正式的，没有医疗及工资保障。
